---
description: Load Rosellas Hackathon project context before coding
alwaysApply: true
---

Before changing code, docs, infrastructure, workflows, or deployment configuration in this repository, read `skills/start-development-session/SKILL.md`, then read `skills/start-development-session/references/project-context.md`.

Use that skill directory as the canonical project context for:

- architecture and service boundaries;
- local commands and verification;
- backend and frontend runtime configuration;
- API paths and data shape;
- Cloud Run and GitHub Actions deployment notes.

For current deployed URLs and GCP/GitHub console links, read `docs/google-infra-links.md`.
